    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;m so sorry for your loss, Molly. Losing someone like that is so incredibly painful, even if they are ready to go. All the stuff, you never think about that, and then they&#39;re gone, and it&#39;s there. Going through it when my mom died was very cathartic, I think. I kept her library card and it makes me smile because I remember how important it was to her. That as an uneducated immigrant, she learned to read, and went to adult night school to get her high school diploma. Stuff like that.<br />Anyway, you wrote about it beautifully. I hope you are doing okay.<br />And, will definitely try the cinnamon toast.</p>
