    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>The cinnamon toast your grandma made is an Upper Peninsula of Michigan culinary tradition called &#8220;Trenary Toast&#8221;. (there&#39;s a small town called Trenary in the U.P.) Is your grandma of Finnish descent?  It&#39;s a traditional food from Finland called korpu.  Many Finlanders emigrated to Michigan&#39;s U.P. during the 1800s&#8230;</p>
    </div>

